column5: Hey all, first report here...been reading others' and it's time to give a little back.  The fishing was tough, but rewarding.... learned some new techniques and had a blast. Casting 15 - 18 ft leads was very challenging but I did manage one fish that went on a couple of exhilarating runs. What a rush! Can't wait to get back.  Here's a pic  Enjoy!
Nice fish bud!!! Tip: use a slip float when casting such long leads.  Take care
Thanks silvio.  Guides and line were freezing, so we pegged the slip float in place.
I see well good job bud.
